        {
          "id": "C.II.1",
          "title": "Case — Outputs",
          "heading_level": 3,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "prose",
              "iaja": "A",
              "ratings": [
                {
                  "grade": "A",
                  "attr": "unit economics"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Unit economics read A — lifting cost in the low $2s per MMBtu puts Novatek on the left tail of the global LNG cost curve. This is not a claim; it is visible in the 5-year operating cost disclosure cross-checked against the Wood Mackenzie field-level series."
            },
            {
              "type": "prose",
              "iaja": "J",
              "text": "Capital allocation rates C because the Yamal-1 overrun and 2021 buyback mistiming show mixed judgement at inflection points. Not a disqualifier; something to watch for recurrence."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "C.II.2",
          "title": "Case — Foundations",
          "heading_level": 3,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "prose",
              "iaja": "J",
              "ratings": [
                {
                  "grade": "D",
                  "attr": "management & governance"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Quis nostrud exercitation. The governance rating is the single biggest reason this may not survive ESA. Sanctions, sanctions risk, opacity of shareholder register, and the Mikhelson position all compound."
            },
            {
              "type": "bullet_group",
              "items": [
                {
                  "text": "Change capacity: Arctic-2 FID shows the company can execute mega-projects on schedule."
                },
                {
                  "text": "Moat durability: resource base extends 40y+; logistics replicable only with 5y lead time."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "C.II.3",
          "title": "Case — Checks",
          "heading_level": 3,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "prose",
              "text": "Lorem ipsum. Checks clear: no material accounting aggression, no outstanding short-seller case of note, one well-managed incident (Sabetta logistics snag, 2024). Disclosure is thin versus Western peers — flag for ESA but not a red line."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "C.II.4",
          "title": "Case — Fitness-for-fighting",
          "heading_level": 3,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "prose",
              "iaja": "A",
              "text": "Catalyst density is high — 4 identifiable events in the next 12m: winter balance outcome (Mar), Yamal-2 COD (Jun), EU LNG quota policy (Sep), Q3 prints (Nov). Good fit for our event-driven style."
            },
            {
              "type": "prose",
              "iaja": "J",
              "text": "Headline volatility is the main mismatch. We'd need to size smaller than a standard GARP name to respect the me-state constraint."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "C.II.5",
          "title": "Case — Setup classification",
          "heading_level": 3,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "callout",
              "tone": "classification",
              "iaja": "J",
              "text": "Classification: Demand-Driven EPSU (primary) + Supply-Reset EPT (secondary). Lineage match = CARLB 2023 thesis. That playbook applies with one modification — RUB-denominated earnings need a currency overlay we didn't run for CARLB."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "D": {
      "letter": "D",
      "title": "COMPONENTS",
      "applicable": true,
      "inline_verdict": "KDICs isolated; two ACHs still open",
      "default_open": false,
      "subsections": [
        {
          "id": "D.I",
          "title": "Mechanics / building blocks",
          "heading_level": 3,
          "target_words": 1050,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "bluf",
              "text": "Investment case rests on one Primary Driver (LNG price path) and one structural hygiene factor (cost-curve position). Both look robust at Triaging. One Key Confusion (Yamal-2 contract mix) must clear before ESA promotion, and one Key Risk (sanctions) must be sized rather than solved."
            }
          ],
          "topics": [
            {
              "id": "D.I.1",
              "title": "KDICs -- Key Drivers of Investment Case",
              "target_words": 300,
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "type": "bluf",
                  "text": "One Primary Driver dominates: LNG price path N1-3Y. Two Secondaries provide supporting mechanics on volume and mix. Tertiaries are noted but de-prioritised. The structure is single-PD and the financial path is simple -- price times volume -- which helps conviction but also means concentration risk lives at the top of the tree."
                },
                {
                  "type": "tree",
                  "title": "KDICs tree -- qualitative drivers to financial outputs",
                  "tiers": [
                    {
                      "label": "PDs",
                      "name": "Primary Drivers",
                      "items": [
                        {
                          "text": "LNG realised price N1-3Y",
                          "detail": "TTF base-case EUR28-35/MWh through 2027; dominates revenue AND unit margin simultaneously",
                          "iaja": "J"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "label": "SDs",
                      "name": "Secondary Drivers",
                      "items": [
                        {
                          "text": "Yamal-2 volume ramp",
                          "detail": "Volume adder through 2027, but price-dependent for margin impact",
                          "iaja": "A"
                        },
                        {
                          "text": "Contract vs spot mix",
                          "detail": "Governs how much of price upside is captured; unresolved -- see D.I.3",
                          "iaja": "A"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "label": "TDs",
                      "name": "Tertiary Drivers",
                      "items": [
                        {
                          "text": "RUB/USD -- noise",
                          "detail": "Largely USD-denominated revenue; cost base partially RUB; net is small"
                        },
                        {
                          "text": "Opex inflation",
                          "detail": "Structural trend, slow-moving; unlikely to shift thesis N1-3Y"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "label": "LIs",
                      "name": "Leading Indicators (of ICDs)",
                      "items": [
                        {
                          "text": "EU storage refill pace",
                          "detail": "Real-time TTF proxy; check weekly",
                          "iaja": "T"
                        },
                        {
                          "text": "Sabetta shipment count",
                          "detail": "Monthly; validates Yamal-2 ramp",
                          "iaja": "T"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "bullet_group",
                  "items": [
                    {
                      "iaja": "J",
                      "text": "Structure is clean -- one PD with a direct financial translation; no cross-effects between variables to muddle the mechanics.",
                      "sub": [
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "PD flows to revenue via realised price x volume; margin is near-linear on price given fixed-cost-heavy production economics."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "I",
                          "text": "Rule-of-thumb sensitivity: every EUR5/MWh on TTF equals approx $800m incremental EBITDA at current volume base."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "I",
                          "text": "Peer comparison: Cheniere, Shell IG unit and Equinor all show similar leverage profile, so the sensitivity is not an outlier -- it is the norm for LNG exposure."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "J",
                      "text": "SDs are conditional on the PD: Yamal-2 volume only creates EBITDA upside if price holds, otherwise the ramp simply offsets compression.",
                      "sub": [
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "If TTF drops to bear-case EUR18-22, the volume ramp masks price compression rather than adds to it -- EBITDA flat, not up."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "Conversely, if TTF holds above EUR30, Yamal-2 is pure upside -- both revenue and margin move together."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "I",
                          "text": "First Yamal-2 train COD is guided for late-2026; full three-train ramp by end-2027 per company IR day May 2025."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "J",
                      "text": "TDs are genuine noise over the horizon -- FX and opex inflation won't shift the thesis, so we don't monitor them actively.",
                      "sub": [
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "RUB-USD hedging is partial but sufficient to keep cash-flow conversion within a tight band regardless of spot FX."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "ACT",
                      "text": "Pull ICD monitoring sheet for LIs 1-2; confirm real-time feeds available from FactSet and wire into weekly review."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "summary",
                  "text": "One-driver cases are the cleanest to own -- but they carry concentration risk. Size accordingly; don't overload."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "D.I.2",
              "title": "KHF/As -- Key Hygiene Factors / Assumptions",
              "target_words": 0,
              "stage_note": "Triaging: n.a. -- hypothesise only if disqualifying. Full treatment at ESA.",
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "type": "bluf",
                  "text": "At Triaging, no KHFs identified that would disqualify. Structural cost-curve position assumed stable N1-3Y; to be stress-tested at ESA."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "D.I.3",
              "title": "KCs/KUs -- Key Confusions & Unknowns",
              "target_words": 300,
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "type": "bluf",
                  "text": "Two live confusions. One is structurally important and could kill the thesis (Yamal-2 contract mix); the other is solvable with a modelling pass (RUB-hedged economics). KC-1 is the main blocker for ESA promotion."
                },
                {
                  "type": "bullet_group",
                  "items": [
                    {
                      "iaja": "J",
                      "text": "KC-1 (structural): What fraction of Yamal-2 LNG is pre-sold into long-dated take-or-pay contracts vs left exposed to spot?",
                      "sub": [
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "If more than 70% is pre-sold, spot price upside is capped -- and the PD weakens materially, since the thesis rests on captured price upside through 2027."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "If between 40-70% pre-sold, the case still works but requires a modelled blend rather than a clean PD narrative."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "I",
                          "text": "Company disclosure is silent on contract split; peers (Cheniere, Shell) disclose approximately 85-90% contracted which is the industry norm."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "I",
                          "text": "Russian state gas strategy post-2022 has historically favoured long-dated Asian offtake agreements, which suggests a higher-than-peer pre-sold ratio is plausible."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "OQ",
                          "text": "Open question: Do any sell-side models address this directly? AlphaSense search scheduled for week of 27-Apr-26."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "J",
                      "text": "KC-2 (solvable): How much of headline EBITDA converts to USD free cash flow after RUB-denominated opex and capex net of available hedges?",
                      "sub": [
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "Reported headline EBITDA is in USD but the underlying cost base is roughly 40% RUB. Hedge ratio and tenor remain unclear from public filings."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "Modelling implication: even a 5-8% FX drag on cash conversion is material at position-size decision level, especially for a concentrated 5-15 name book."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "I",
                          "text": "2023 disclosure implied roughly 8-12% FX drag on cash conversion over the full year -- small in isolation but cumulatively meaningful."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "ACT",
                      "text": "Build minimal Excel scenario for KC-2 before ESA kickoff (2-day task). Escalate KC-1 to AlphaSense deep research with explicit ask for contract-split disclosure."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "summary",
                  "text": "KC-1 is the one that can kill the thesis. If it fails to clear at ESA, park the name cleanly rather than push on with a weakened PD."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "D.I.4",
              "title": "KRs -- Key Concerns / Risks",
              "target_words": 300,
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "type": "bluf",
                  "text": "Three material risks, all headline-adjacent and none small. Sanctions is the main source of tail risk and probably not fully solvable; Yamal-2 execution is the main source of base-case risk; governance opacity is a reputational drag rather than a cash-flow threat."
                },
                {
                  "type": "bullet_group",
                  "items": [
                    {
                      "iaja": "J",
                      "text": "KR-1: Sanctions tightening -- tail risk, hard to size, cannot be eliminated through analysis alone.",
                      "sub": [
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "Secondary sanctions on Asian buyers would re-route volumes but keep them sellable -- disruptive but not binary at the cash-flow level."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "Full SDN listing on Novatek itself would be binary for ADR holders but remains unlikely absent a new geopolitical shock of material magnitude."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "I",
                          "text": "Base-rate from 2022-25: 3 of 12 sanctioned Russian energy names suffered binary outcomes for foreign holders -- 25% base rate on binary outcome is non-trivial."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "I",
                          "text": "Current market pricing implies roughly 10-15% probability of SDN listing over 24m per CDS proxy -- market thinks it's possible, not imminent."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "J",
                      "text": "KR-2: Yamal-2 execution -- base-case risk, most likely to materialise as a schedule slip rather than a project failure.",
                      "sub": [
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "6-month COD slip would push volume ramp into a weaker part of the TTF cycle, turning a modelled 2026 contribution into essentially a 2027 event."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "I",
                          "text": "Arctic-2 COD was on time despite sanctions pressure -- track record is favourable but not a guarantee for Yamal-2 given tighter Western equipment supply chain."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "J",
                      "text": "KR-3: Governance opacity -- reputational drag, not a financial risk in the conventional sense.",
                      "sub": [
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "Ultimate shareholder structure is opaque post-2022 re-registration. Creates me-state friction and complicates any compliance review but has no direct cash-flow impact."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "ACT",
                      "text": "At ESA, build an explicit kill-switch list tied to each KR; define position adjustments for each level-1 trigger (e.g. halve on SDN news, exit on binary confirmation)."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "summary",
                  "text": "Two sizing constraints emerge: smaller starter than a standard GARP name; and no add on KR-1 triggers until the tail event probability has been re-priced."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "D.I.5",
              "title": "KPOs -- Key Positive Optionality",
              "target_words": 150,
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "type": "bluf",
                  "text": "Two non-modelled optionalities worth flagging. Neither is required for the base case to work -- they are upside toppers rather than load-bearing."
                },
                {
                  "type": "bullet_group",
                  "items": [
                    {
                      "iaja": "J",
                      "text": "KPO-1: Buyback re-initiation -- plausible but not scheduled.",
                      "sub": [
                        {
                          "iaja": "A",
                          "text": "Net cash at $2.4bn vs $1.1bn prior year; balance sheet permits, and capital allocation signalling is due at next full-year results."
                        },
                        {
                          "iaja": "I",
                          "text": "No buyback announced since 2021; management cited \"capital allocation review\" at FY25 results without committing to a specific channel."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "J",
